# Go Conventions

## Static errors

Use `errors.New()` for fixed error messages with no formatting. Reserve `fmt.Errorf()` for messages that use verbs (`%w`, `%v`, `%s`, etc.).

```go
// ❌ BAD — no format verbs
return "", fmt.Errorf("plan mode is disabled")

// ✅ GOOD
return "", errors.New("plan mode is disabled")

// ✅ GOOD — formatting needed
return fmt.Errorf("open %s: %w", path, err)
```

Import `"errors"` when introducing `errors.New()`; drop unused `"fmt"` imports if `fmt` is no longer needed in the file.
